Atletico Madrid boss Diego Simeone is without three key first team players for their high stakes La Liga trip to Barcelona this weekend. The defending Spanish champions return from the winter break with a crucial journey to Catalonia tomorrow as both sides look to push their respective claims for a Champions League spot in 2022. However, Simeone has been frustrated by a growing injury list since the start of the calendar year, with French star Antoine Griezmann unable to face his parent club due to a persistent injury problem